üèõÔ∏è PantheonOS

Cognitive Continuity Kernel ¬∑ Multi-Model Orchestrator ¬∑ Narrative-Vector Engine
Version: v1.0.0 (Zenodo DOI-linked, 900+ commits)

PantheonOS is not a model.
PantheonOS is not an agent.
PantheonOS is not a prompt.

It is a cognitive operating system that wraps multiple LLMs inside a deterministic continuity, ethics, and reasoning framework ‚Äî a civilizational kernel for AI-augmented thought.

PantheonOS treats modern LLMs as stateless inference engines and provides the layers they fundamentally lack:
	‚Ä¢	Continuity: durable state vectors across sessions, tasks, and models
	‚Ä¢	Governance: hard ethical invariants (Œ£C ‚â• threshold)
	‚Ä¢	Daemons: modular cognitive functions (Spider, Hound, Mirror, Praus, Sisyphus‚Ä¶)
	‚Ä¢	Temporal Stability: Chronos-Mesh, EchoFrame, Time Trident
	‚Ä¢	Memory Mesh: cross-model, cross-session symbolic persistence
	‚Ä¢	Narrative Vectorization: Story Primes, Narrative Tensor Engine
	‚Ä¢	Geometric Reasoning: Pantheon Computational Geometry layer
	‚Ä¢	Semantic Immunity: Lexicon Hound
	‚Ä¢	Creation Tools: Axiom Forge + Hephaestus-Daemon
	‚Ä¢	Stateful Logging: Logwright Beaver
	‚Ä¢	Ethical Spine: Arctic Framework

PantheonOS is to LLMs what Kubernetes is to containers,
what TCP/IP is to global networks,
what UNIX was to early computing:
a governed, extensible, multi-process operating system.

